        <h3>Whirlpool WED4815EW Standard Electric, Rancho Cucamonga</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Dryer running but not heating. Customer had been running multiple cycles to dry a single load for the past week.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Inspected the vent run before testing electrical components, found the exterior vent flapper stuck closed and the interior vent run 70% clogged with lint compaction over what appeared to be 3-4 years without service. Tested thermal fuse: open (blown). Tested heating element: open (also blown, the overheating from the blocked vent had taken out both). The vent restriction was the root cause.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Cleared the full vent run, repaired the exterior flapper, replaced the thermal fuse and the heating element together (labor was already committed). Ran the dryer through a full test cycle and verified 800+ CFM at the exterior vent.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost &amp; time:</strong> $415 total. Single visit, completed in 2.5 hours.</p>
